 BY BANYO TEMITAYO BILLIONAIRE businessman, Bolu Akin-Olugbade, is dead. He was said to have died on Wednesday from complications related to COVID-19 at a Lagos hospital. He was aged 64. Akin-Olugbade, who was the Aare Ona Kakanfo of Owu Kingdom, attended Corona School, Yaba; King’s College, Lagos; London University; University of California; and Cambridge University, where he obtained his doctorate degree in Company Law. His business interests cut across law, property development, construction, manufacturing, logistics, distribution, maritime/offshore services, and investment banking, among others. Details later…  